title: Anne of Green Gables (version 3)
creator: Lucy Maud Montgomery
description: LibriVox recording of Anne of Green Gables by Lucy Maud Montgomery. Read by Karen Savage. The timeless story of the young orphan girl sent by accident to a brother and sister who had wanted a boy, Anne, with her vivid imagination and sensitive spirit, has enchanted readers for generations. (Summary by Karen Savage) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. M4B audiobook of complete book
subject: librivox; audiobook; anne; green gables; fiction
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody: I'm extremely obliged to you for reading this wonderful book. You have such a sweet voice, it was so pleasant to listen. I hope that you'll record more.
Thoroughly delightful book, read by Karen Savage with absolute perfection. One the best audio books on Librivox, or anywhere else!
Probably the most enjoyable audio book I've listened to so far.
